Yay peeps... I'm back in kdrama Lala Land

So much of choices that left me undecided on which I would love to focus on especially after Playful Kiss. So Ding Ding Ding and we have a winner here... I have found my new drug to keep me addicted to Kdrama. It's Secret Garden, airing on SBS on Saturday-Sunday slot. Why?

Secret Garden


The Plot

Body swapping between lead characters, how can you say no to that? Although we've been told with the main plot quite early on but I just love the introduction of the characters leading to that body swapping twist. It was done quite subtly not just for the sake of introducing all characters in the show. The flow was just right and for the first time I feel so confident to say that this is one hell of a gem that I'm desperately seeking out in this year. After the disappointment of Coffee House and My Girlfriend is A Gumiho, I might say that this is promising to be the best Kdrama for the year. I'd hope I'm right. coz the feeling was so right and I even get shivers just by Hyun Bin's stare.

Kim Joo Won - Hyun Bin
What can I say? He's cold, he's rich, he's sarcastically funny, selfish and too into himself, yeah you could say he's the typical male lead character we found in Kdrama, but I have to stop you right there. He is the most interesting male lead character I have known so far coz not only he's a chaebol, but he comes with an excess bagage; a weirdly challengely fashion sense and total whacked-nut-job for his own fear and unusual taste in women. He's so interestingly to hate but love to adore. Especially when he keeps thinking about GRI and continue to fantasize about her; the most notable scene is when he was totally surprised when the hallucinated GRI talk to him back, I was laughing till I cry.

Gil Ra Im - Ha Ji Won
Wew... I never been so attracted to a female before in my life. Cool is not even a word to describe her. And I totally get why KJW is overly smitten by her presence. HJW is really an amazing actress. Not only she portrays the character to be so slick, cool and hi-chic but also girlish and vulnerable like any normal girl would be. I just love her.

My weekends would never been the same.


p/s : That sparkling tracksuit really makes me giggle each time. LOL all the way.

Hi hi friends...

Just dropping by a while...
I'm having withdrawal symptoms of Playful Kiss... thankfully tomorrow its YT episode time... wakaka
So in the mean time here I go...
I also post my thoughts on Soompi thread.

My quick sum-up on PK vs ISWAK/TKA vs INK vs Anime
1. Anime is still the best series. PK comes in second. INK third and ISWAK/TKA would be last, sorry (>.<)
2. Jung So-Min plays the best Kotoko.
3. Takashi Kashiwabara plays the best Naoki. Sorry KHJ, u came in 3rd after Joe Cheng.
4. Superb casting is by far PK is the best. From main to supporting, all are eye-candy and great. Why? Keep reading.
5. The best mom is indeed PK. Not annoying just lovable to hate.
6. The best Yuuki is also PK. Cute like in anime.
7. The best Kinnosuke is again from PK. I never felt sympathy for this guy, yet in PK I do.
8. The best best-friend (Jinko and Satomi) yet again, must I say PK?
9. The best dads for both Naoki and Kotoko. Hmm actually its a tie. I like INK and PK.
10. The best Reiko, raise ur hands with me if u say PK. She is funny and likes to tease Oh Hani.
11. The best Sudou is of coz Mr 40. Haha I really like him. Funny hair flip.
12. The best house set-up, PK of coz. That window, it's really is something.
13. The best comedy. INK is over-the-top. Anime is cartoonish. ISWAK/TKA bleh. So I think PK is the best. The chicken hood? LOL
14. The most letdown scene - The scoreboard-exam revelation day. Come on! What?! A graph chart?!
15. The most heartfelt moment - The practice wedding walk by Oh Hani and dad.
16. The most meaningful moment - The swing scene between Joon-Gu and Oh Hani.
17. The most giddy moment - Too many to say in here, LOL
18. The most mixed feeling scene (love&hate) - Car kissing scene. Its too dark and I can't see them. Bleh...
19. The most hateful scene - The scoreboard. I still hate it, coz that's the essence of their relationship. The beginning.
20. The most loveable scene - When Oh Hani finds Baek Seung-jo waiting for her for their date. His look is full of love.
21. The best twist from manga - Baek Seung-jo kept looking at Oh Hani during their first breakfast. OMG that was HOT!!!
22. The most satisfying scene - The look on Baek Seung-jo after Oh Hani's kiss attack on their wedding day. LOL
23. The best episode? - I'd say Episode 15, keke... yeah bcoz of the wedding n honeymoon baby!
24. The worst episode? - I'd say the first. It fail to capture audience, if I was new to the INK franchise.
25. So I think it's best to say that PK is the best live-action adaptation. Anime just stay on-top of the crops coz it represent the whole essence from manga briefly.

Note : PK : Playful Kiss l ISWAK : It Started With A Kiss l TKA : They Kiss Again l INK : Itazura Na Kiss

Anyway, with the recent event happening in eka, I got a little carried away and really angry towards the action of re-uploading to youtube. So, here's what I thought if I was in the culprit shoes.. just playing

1) WHO ARE YOU TO FEEL ANGRY FOR? IT'S NOT YOUR VIDEO ANYWAY... Yes. If it's not ours then it certainly not yours too. Then, why do you want to upload? Let's say you're right. Let's say that we shouldn't be angry because of this. Then, please dont be angry if we decide not to share any of our subbing anymore. We have nothing to lose. We're subbing for our own sake and friends. Since the copyright issue in Asia is still not as strict as in certain parts of the world, we thought we could take that advantage and share it with everybody under certain ruled community. By uploading to youtube and other sites, these rules might bite us in the end. We dont want that to happen. Called us paranoid, whatever... but we are aware of this unwanted scenarios. Do you?

2) HUH, CLAIMING THAT YOU WANT TO SHARE WITH THE PUBLIC BUT WHY LOCK THE COMMUNITY? I'M DOING THESE OUTSIDERS A FAVOUR!! The terms locked community is only for outsiders who are not belong to our community. Whether because they didnt know about us or chose not to join us coz they didn't feel the needs to follow our request. So, as far as I'm concerned, our releases it is considered public. A favour for an outsider is to have them join the community and they can start sharing.

3) YOUTUBE OR OTHER STREAMING SITES WILL FURTHER PROMOTE MORE FANS... WHY ARE U AGAINST THIS 'HOLY" ACTION? If your intention for uploading is to promote, wow you'e the most loyal fans out there arent you? Having the time and energy to upload the files rather than promoting our community instead. If you really want to upload, please use the right way in the first place. Ask for permission.

4) PERMISSION? WHY DO I NEED TO ASK? YOU WILL REJECT ME FOR SURE!! Yes, since we already stated firmly in the very beginning that uploading is not allowed. We're very SORRY to reject your request even when you already know that we are strongly against it. Yes, nobody likes rejection. So as we when you reject our rules and still want to upload. I guess the feeling is mutual.

5) THEN WHAT THE HECK, I CAN DO WHATEVER I WANT.. I CAN UPLOAD AS MANY VIDEOS I WANT... Hmmm, if you think like that, then what can we do? So keep doing what you're doing. Don't worry, we wil do our part as well. We'lll keep track and take down any uploaded videos which relates to us. You can count on that.

p/s : Did I play that role? Hahaha... kinda like Dr Jeckyll and Mrs Hyde there.. hope that may be we'll understand on their perception and just what the hell they were thinking; doing such things...

Haha... I'm so cynical at the moment. I knew I had seen it coming and I wished I could say this right to their not-so-ashamed faces...
"SEE, I TOLD YOU SO..."

The best part is now I really don't feel angry at all only a huge smirk on my face...
And I'm just glad that I'm friends who share the same vision and continuously scoff off those mindless ignorant people...

BACK THEN, those individuals scolded and ranted about how we run things... and how  we should've follow their way and bragging about how their intentions are much more high, pure and genuine compared to us and we should've been sensitive about their crappy-feelings... WTF? And during that hectic time,  we silently excused ourselves from that HOLY and ELITE community, coz we know that we're not welcome and what we're doing is basically 'violating' their RULES (self-proclaimed by certain individuals)...

NOW? I believed that so-called place had become a place what they have accused us doing... that is promoting? With recent turn of events, I GUESS IT'S OKAY FOR THEM TO PROMOTE.... BUT NOT US... And probably we'll hear excuses saying... Hey, it's not a promotion! It's more like an announcement... Hmmm... So, is there any difference to what we're doing back then? Yes? Oh, so it's different just because of the 12 hours or 24 hours unlock thingy? So, in our case it's called promoting? What about them? No? Oh I forgot, because of the 12 hours freedom-to-download?.. HECK! It's still call PROMOTING! Right? Potato... Potato..

And shouldn't this individual or community been thrown out by now or silently excuse themselves? Hmmm No? Huh, I guess some people really are not ashamed for themselves and that they are simply didn't have any pride...

NOW I feel pity at them too... but hey! That's just ME! There's a lot more that I wanted to say but I guess I save it for my next cynical remarks... I really love to gun them down >()<

p/s : Don't this people tired of making excuses?

Where should I begin...

I prefer Terminator : Salvation although I'm really a fan of transformer but somehow as expected, the sequel, Transformer : Revenge of the Fallen yet again missed the mark and failed to impressed me.

WARNING : SPOILER!

WHAT!!!! How can I say such things...

I know that big bang-fight-to-death scenes with Optimus dying and Megatron bullying his twin, Starscream (I honestly can't recognize him without his signature red & blue colour, wonder where went wrong) I know it's not important but that tiny details actually important to a fan like me to be excited about this significant character, without the colour and also that very annoying voice, Starscream could be change name to Megadeath for all I care. Half of the movie I get tired already with this not-so-important character, the mom, the dad, the girlfriend oh not to forget the robo-girl-tounge and the idiot friend who really likes his stunt gun. Even Constructicons didn't get proper introduction... or it's just a big-fat vacuum machine? Shrieks!!! I seriously don't like what I'm seeing... I guess I like it more if they focussed more on the robots rather than the humans... BORING! I'm yawning like hell! I'm halfway on my sleep, even when the 6 primes suddenly appears. I was like, WTF?

For terminator, I'm just at awe with the sequence. Yes, this was done brilliantly as to how they kept us engaging to Marcus, a new character which I already  guess a skynet tool to get to John Connor but I really didn't expect to see Mr Senator in his old young bod. I seriously can recall back to his condition way back from the very first terminator. Bulky as ever and looks very young too. That kind of details really contribute to my amazement. Not to mention the ever so cool moto-terminator which I really wish to have someday!! HAHA keep on dreaming! The story is brief and simple and the scenes were done without left me so much question in the head, even the big question still makes me anticipates more and more towards the ending. Although I have to admit the scenes where Marcus was electro-resurrected was really funny but it does makes logic as to why he still remains a man in a tin body.

Both has pros and cos, without a doubt Transformers is a BIG DEAL and the scenes were spectacular BUT to be better, lose the human a bit, let the autobots and decepticons really steal the light this time.

Just like the story I find myself lately in an aimless mode...

Episode 18 preview, translated from KBS:

“That young lady is like a lotus flower that can make mud clear. Hold her dearly (in high esteem). She’s a lotus who can make a family for you.”

As her mind struggles with all the events that occurred at the resort, Jan Di finds temporary peace at a Buddhist temple that she visits with Ji Hu on their way back to Seoul. However, when she arrives home, she is greeted with the news that her parents have decided to move to a fishing village.
Similar to HanaDan Series.

Jun Pyo hears about the particulars regarding Jan Di’s [shoulder] injury from Yi Jeong and belatedly feels both guilt and regret. Jan Di, who has moved into a rooftop room [with her brother], is surprised when Jun Pyo unexpectedly shows up as her neighbour.
This shoulder thing with Jan-di is a new twist in korean version. It's good enough to make Jun-pyo worry about Jan-di. Can't wait to see Jun Pyo living as commoner.

Ga Eul takes courage from her conversation with Eun Jae when she is told that it isn’t good for love to remain hidden or suppressed, and asks Yi Jeong out on a date. He firmly rejects her, but then turns up a few days later with a resolute expression in front of Ga Eul as she is leaving work.
Also this is new promising twist that the korean make. hopefully something would happen. I felt shame that those two never get together, either in HanaDan, MG or HYD... totally lame!

Read further for more spoilers!

General spoilers:

  • Jan Di is thrown from seeing Jae Gyeong and Jun Pyo together. Seeing that Jan Di feels depressed, Ji Hu comforts her. Typical...annoying!
  • Jun Pyo ultimately rejects Jae Gyeong’s advances. Jae Gyeong sits in her room alone, gloomily eating ice cream as she realizes that Jun Pyo must have been Jan Di’s boyfriend. I guess this shows how strong Jae Kyung is rather than her predecessor in 2 versions.
  • The next morning, she tells Jan Di that she didn’t get any sleep because her and Jun Pyo had an eventful (”historic”) night together. She says that Jun Pyo left early because he was embarrassed and that she’s leaving now to follow him “like a thread follows a needle”. Once Jae Gyeong leaves Ji Hu and Jan Di’s presence, she sheds tears. Typical plot and yet it show Jae Kyung jealous side which we never see before.
  • Jan Di and Ji Hu visit a Buddhist temple and make wishes - (hers regarding university acceptance and his regarding happiness). I guess this is just a way for Jan-di to breath and absorb all this madness ahaha
  • Jan Di’s parents find work by the coast and move to the seaside where Jan Di’s uncle lives, leaving Jan Di and her brother to find a cheap place to live in. Typical plotline.
  • Jun Pyo moves into a nearby room (presumably to watch over Jan Di’s safety). Oh Jun-pyo as commoner. Cant wait! Promising comical plots in here, I hope.
  • During pottery class, Eun Jae and Ga Eul converse. Eun Jae encourages Ga Eul to confess her feelings to the person she likes. Eventually, Ga Eul goes to Yi Jeong’s house and surprises him by asking him out on a date. He initially turns her down. BOF spoiler episode 17 & 18

“Don’t forget. There’s a bond (love)that only comes once in a lifetime. The real thing only comes once. It’s another cruel truth.” — KP’s note: We did some research, and we believe Yi Jeong says this to Ga Eul.

As momentum builds for the merger of Shin-hwa Group and JK Group, Jun Pyo and Jae Gyeong go on their first date. Unfortunately, each part of the date that Jae Gyeong has planned reminds Jun Pyo of Jan Di. Jae Gyeong senses Jun Pyo’s thoughts [of someone else] and feeling insecure, demands a kiss. Ji Hu and Jan Di are conversing on the emergency exit stairwell at the time and witness the two…….

When Yi Jeong comes across his father with another woman in Yi Jeong’s own workshop, he has a big argument with his dad. In the midst of his troubled mood, vague memories of his first love Eun Jae arise. Out of her feelings for Yi Jeong, Ga Eul decides to enroll for pottery lessons. After she registers, she meets Cha Eun Jae, a student-teacher with a lovely smile.

Although Eun Jae loved Yi Jeong when she was younger, nothing came of it because he thought she was in love with his older brother. When Yi Jeong meets her again, he finds out that she is now actually his brother’s girlfriend.

Although he denied believing in a single fated love to Ga Eul, Eun Jae indirectly reveals Yi Jeong’s true view on love and destiny. She also contributes to Ga Eul and Yi Jeong’s growing relationship.

Updated (2/26): Unconfirmed major spoilers for episodes 17 & 18

  • Jan Di works hard at various jobs in order to help out her parents, but collapses while in front of Ji Hu at the art centre. He watches over her at her bedside, and kisses her hand.
  • Jun Pyo and Jae Gyeong’s first date destination is a grocery store. At first, Jun Pyo eats alone, completely indifferent to Jae Gyeong. However, in the end, they eat together in the food court - even feeding each other!
  • The couple then goes to Namsan. However, thoughts of Jan Di keep rising in Jun Pyo’s mind. Jae Gyeong sees “Jun Pyo ♥ Jan Di - first night” in the cable car, and begins to piece their past together.
  • Due to Jun Pyo’s continual inattention, Jae Gyeong demands that Jun Pyo proves that he likes her. This results in a kiss on campus - witnessed by Jan Di and Ji Hu.
  • Jun Pyo and Ji Hu meet up sometime after this happens. At that time, Ji Hu explodes on Jun Pyo and tells him the reason that Jan Di can no longer swim (- she took the blow that was meant for Jun Pyo). Finally, Jun Pyo realizes what happened.
  • Jan Di and Ji Hu visit a Buddhist temple and make wishes - (hers regarding university acceptance and his regarding happiness).
  • Assuming that Jan Di and Ji Hu are a couple, Jae Gyeong persuades them to go on a double date with herself and Jun Pyo. They leave for an impromptu holiday.
  • While in the pool, Jan Di starts to sink due to a case of anemia (iron deficiency). In contrast to the manga, Jun Pyo (not Ji Hu) jumps in to save her. When Jan Di expresses surprise at Jun Pyo being able to swim, he explains about the time in New Caledonia when he could only stand by and watch as Ji Hu saved Jan Di. He says, “I learned how to swim because I thought it’d be easier to face drowning in water rather than watching another guy save you first again.” Jan Di is touched by his confession, while Jae Gyeong feels miserable. As Jun Pyo carries Jan Di to [her? his?] room, Ji Hu blocks his path and takes her into his own arms.
  • Hearing noise from the room, Jan Di goes to see if Jae Gyeong is ok. She is shocked to see Jae Gyeong unclothed, embracing Jun Pyo. Seeing that Jan Di feels depressed, Ji Hu wordlessly comforts her.
  • After being rejected by Jun Pyo, Jae Gyeong comes to realize that Jun Pyo and Jan Di must really love each other. She breaks off the engagement, but asks that the business deal between JK Group and Shin-Hwa continue.
  • Jan Di’s parents find work by the coast and move to the seaside, leaving Jan Di and her brother to find a cheap place.
Note: We get these spoilers from a Korean blogger who will not reveal his sources. Hence, we aren’t sure how much of it is true; however, he has been quite reliable up until now.

Yes I'm talking about the same story. Only that each version has it's own pros and cons. here I just want to share my views on why I'm watching this 3 version;

MG 2001
The only thing that glued me to this version is Jerry Yan. Even though his acting is not that good, but he really has that aura to be Dau Ming Si. The plot line really slow and I didn't hesitate to push the forward button sometimes. But since this is the first version that I watched, to me, they really did a good job in setting the drama standard from the adapted manga. As for the chemistry in F4, the relationship between each of them is genuinely good. Each character really potrays themselves as these 4 rich brats who grew up together as friends. I mean if outside I can see them being friends. I didn't regret to collect all the series set, coz I can watch jerry Yan whenever I want hehehehe

HYD 2005
I was really disappointed actually. This is not what I imagine Domyouji would be coz yes I was in the impression of Jerry Yan look-a-like. The storyline much to disappointment, doesn't work for me. Yes, they did some twist and turns but all I can say is that I prefer MG than this. The cast were, sorry to say but I think my least favourites. In a nutshell Domyouji here doesn't portrayed best by Matsu-Jun. No way near. It really gives me a headache. To make matter worse I even bought the series. Kind of regret but since I'm a collector, I guess I have to bear it then...

BBF 2009
To me this is a very refreshing version. Not to say that I like it entirely but seriously Lee Min-Ho is Jerry Yan's twin. I can recall certain shots that I innocently thought that he was Jerry Yan, hahaha. May be because of that I totally cast aside Matsu Jun in HYD. But still... now I'm glued to the show !!^^ Damn you Lee Min-ho aka Jerry Yan!! Anyway, about the storyline, I didn't say that it's the best but I really can say that the writers did a very good job of twisting parts of MG, HYD and the manga itself. Like I said it's refreshing. And also they cast this 4 good looking guys which I can say the best F4 ever. Can't wait to buy the series... hehehehhe

Wahh it's been so long not writing here...

As usual last night watched the crazy 2 days 1 night and yes, this time was a whole a lot of fun. Not that I didn't like them with Chan Ho, but I thought may be the guys held back a bit since they were with someone who is prominent.



This week they went to Beolgyo, a place known for its ark-shell (adik-beradik kerang) digging... wakaka
The boys were offered money so that they can eat and have a fun time at the market place for 2 hours; but the director warned them that they have to pay back by doing some kind of work. As a result;
Su Geun - 200,000 won
Ji Won - 5,000 won
Kim C - 30,000 won
Seung Gi - 30,000 won
Ho Dong - 10,000 won
MC Mong - 4,000 won

Truthfully I was laughing hard when Su Geun asked that big amount coz, he knew what's coming, yet he dares to do it. I guess that's the true entertainment sacrifice. He really wanted to be that centre of attention. Its fun to see him spent the money on others, even at first they were reluctant coz afraid that Su Geun might use that against them later. But seriously Su Geun looked really honest about it. I laughed hard when MC Mong made a remark about how he look like BBF (Boys Before Flowers), then the Paradise song was played in the background....  and I was like O_o... which boys are you talking about? NOOOO!!! It's like night and day, right?

Anyway, after the fun time, they boys headed back and as expected the work that they had to do is ark-shell digging. The Director mentioned that 1 piece of arkshell is equal to 100 won; so
Su Geun - 2,000 ark shell
Ji Won - 50 arkshell
Kim C - 300 arkshell
Seung Gi - 300 arkshell
Ho Dong - 100 arkshell
MC Mong - 40 arkshell

At this moment the director was very strict in saying that they had to deliver thier work and no discount what so ever. Hearing this, Su Geun silently marched down at the edge of the jetty and acted like he wanted to jump off. I was laughing really hard. So they boys went off and started digging at the beach area.

After certain time, the tide was rising, so they had to stop and everybody managed to get their quota... except for Su Geun; he was short 1,500 arkshells. So he was given another chance to dig, either at 2.00 am or 2.00 pm. Hearing this, the boys jumped at it and said, "You should do it at 2.00 am," and then director sensing this turn of event offered him a 33% discount. He only need to fing 1,000 pieaces instead. Then Su Geun wanted to make it more interesting," What if the loser of bokbulbok games has to accompany me?" Hearing this, the boys were a bit surprised and really thought that the idea was good & funny but silently they felt like O'oh... O_o

So the 3 games for dinner  this time were hide and seek, quiz and guessing matches in box. Haenam team (Su Geun, Kim C, & MC Mong) team lost to Hodong team (Ho Dong, Seung Gi & Ji Won). Next week we'll get to see who is the lucky person to accompany Su Geun for arkshell digging at 2.00 am... wakakaka

p/s : After watching this, I went to watch BBF again and really crazy over Lee Min-Ho ^^. HUAAA~~

Hi hi...

I just wanna share some silly story... it's about my nieces. Hahaa as I was re-watching Excite!! DVD the other day, they were interested to join with me; one is about 7 years old and the other is 5 years old. Since I'm living with them, I sometimes have to entertain them of course. Then, I asked whether they like these "abang", it means brother, here is polite to call them that rather than just guys... * I really had a hard time trying to ask them this grown up questions... hahaha...

So one thing lead to another the 7 year old said that she likes the yellow coloured t-shirt, the 5 year old well she likes the light green one. And when I asked them who do you think that I like in here, the girls mentioned... the red one... hahaha right on! They are truly my nieces! HAHHAHAHA!!

Then the next day they asked if they can watch it again especially the boogie-woogie medley part (yes, coz it involves colour and lots of dance movement). And of course the eight of being silly as usual. This happens almost every night now. They would sneak up into my room and asked " Can I watch 'abang' dancing again?" Hahaha... 

Then after a while, I'm being the experimenting type of person, like to see whether the girls like to see other JE groups. So I let them watched JE Countdown concerts ( I know that this is boring one but I just want them to see the latest one)... I showed them kanjani8 and they immediately recognised them... how cute! "Here is dark green brother.... here is the purple one... ahhh the red brother... Why is he wearing a pin? Like a girl." then I asked them, "Comel tak?" meaning "Cute isn't he?"... and to my surprise they are nodding... hahaha They still like the boys... then HeySayJump comes into play... the girls watched and also like them coz they are being cute and all... 

Then came Arashi... They danced and as they focused on Ohno, my nieces move back a little from the screen, so I said, "Why? Isn't he cute?"... They are shaking their heads and I was like laughing like hell.. no offense... I didnt say that I like Arashi and I didn't say that I hate them, I simply don't have anything against them but my nieces really cracked me O_o hahaha.. then I point to Matsu Jun, they also shaked their heads... I kept laughing hard... then I point back to dark green brother (Yoko), who accidently was there and the girls nod!...  wow !!! ... You're truly my nieces!!! HAHAHAHA

Sorry for being silly... this is just some baka stories that I think I like to share... again no offense to Arashi... may be the aura devil in OHNO is so strong that my nieces were afraid of them.... 

p/s : the dark green brother... is cute. ^^ I like the curly hair. Red with pin, even cuter. Hehehee

EKA.001 - [2007.12.01] Janiben SP

With the recent happening in eka, ppl say that I've been silent... Well, the thing is I've been away coz I was too busy with my works and couldn't really sit down and absorbed all this madness/ reality... 

First I started subbing so that I could understand and I think it would be good if others can see it too... Thus I recall from way back earlier where the internet is newly introduced and lots of things you could get from there and yes.. it's free... well as long as you pay the bill... I remember that we used to download free stuffs like mp3, movies which yes have their copyright issues thus making downloading as illegal material etc etc... Yes, who wouldn't like to have them for free? I know I do... I kind of sad when they closed down NAPSTER and all but then they introduced the word 'SHARING' ... It's a new way of downloading the thing with a host like u-torrent, limewire etc...  is it still illegal?... We use the word share to avoid illegal issues... hmmm is it similar to what happened here? Or am I rambling without any direction.... 

Ppl can judge and it's quite subjective... Human's Law are breakable... why because we made them. We can bend and amend them in anyway possible... but based on what? Our feelings or logic? Yes, a bit tricky but that's what I'm concerned from this fiesca. Ppl can judge you and label you with anything but the most important thing is your intention. It's pretty simple, really... And our intention is to share... period. It's true that subbing the video is illegal, but hear me out on this, our intention is not. We considered it as sharing and not distributing or making profit out of it. That's why we fight hard for this. 

Ppl say that we're green and new to these situation and that this selling subbed material has been the same all along, and not just with us but others too. Well, it will be the same if we don't do something about it, right? At least with us doing something radical, perhaps we can learn and improve to tackle the problem much better. That's how I see it.

Hip Hip Hooray!

Yes...  I got my result. Its 178/200... so yeah I passed the first aid training.
Now I'm really busy with work... ISO Audit is coming to town! AHHH I really hate them!
